latestPosts.caption:
Thank you for 1.5 million views! To all the trollers: you've either never been to the USA or are too shallow to think positively. I choose to focus on the 13,000 people who liked the video and are standing up for me in the comments section!

A little conversation between me and my daughter…few days back : 

Her: “Why are we even going to Costco like this? It’s not urgent.”
Me: “What do you mean ‘like this’? In a saree?” Are you ashamed ? 
Her: “I’m not ashamed… I just don’t want to go in.”
Me: “But why? You can’t stay in the car. You’re coming with me.
Have you ever seen other cultures shy away from their traditions?
They flaunt it with pride—because it’s theirs.
And we should too. No place, no country asks us to hide who we are.
So why hold back?
Wear your culture. Own it. Be proud of it.
Because confidence starts in small things…
Embrace your color ,traditions and culture like a PRO🥰
Like walking into Costco in a saree.
#sᴛᴏʀʏᴛɪᴍᴇ #motherdaughterconversations

latestPosts.caption:
Missed the Ghibli trend when it was hot, but turns out I needed the animation filter more than ever — because the swimsuit was real, and so was the cleavage anxiety.
So here I am, months late but fully animated. Just a reminder: it’s never too late to hop on a trend... especially when it lets you be brave in your own way .I looked too good in this swimsuit to let it rot in my camera roll — cleavage, sass, and all.
But the fear was real… so I Ghibli-fied it 😜

Tell me in comments section girls where are you watching this from ? What chores exactly you doing ?
